diary entry dated November 15, 1991, the Senator noted that
there was discussion at this meeting about Scott making a
$3,000 contribution to him. Senator Packwood testified that
he does not recall any discussion of the Maislin decision or
the Negotiated Rates Equity Act or the job offer to Mrs.
Packwood in connection with this meeting.

192.   As of February 6, 1991, Mr. Lee continued to hold
open his offer of employment to Mrs. Packwood.  Senator
Packwood does not recall any specific conversations with him
about the job offer at this time.

193.  Senator Packwood corresponded with the ICC regarding
Trailer Train on a number of occasions.

194.  This breakfast meeting is referenced in a letter dated
